title: QI - Series A to M
description:
Tv show QI From the begining, serie A, to serie M 
+ "the making of QI" Documentary on the tv show.

QI (Quite Interesting) is a British comedy panel game 

television quiz show created and co-produced by John 

Lloyd, hosted by Stephen Fry, and featuring permanent 

panellist Alan Davies. Most of the questions are 

extremely obscure, making it unlikely that the correct 

answer will be given. To compensate, points are awarded 

not only for right answers, but also for interesting 

ones, regardless of whether they are right or even 

relate to the original question. Conversely, points are 

deducted from a panellist who gives "answers which are 

not only wrong, but pathetically obvious
Wikipedia


Later shows only have subtitles.
All Episodes are Xl from serie G and on
